    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/77">Heinricus</persName> divina favente clementia tertius
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si circa
                        sanctorum loca benefitia condigna impendimus, hoc nostram imperialem
                        maiestatem condecere credimus, insuper et aeterna premia nos inde adipisci
                        confidimus. Quapropter omnium Christi nostrorumque fidelium universitatem
                        scire volumus, qualiter nos ob amorem Christi et eius genitricis virginis
                        Marie ac per interventum <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Widricus"
                                >Withrici</name></persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/223">Placentini</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchionis</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke"><name ref="Warnerius"
                            >Warnerii</name></persName> nobis dilectissimi atque fidelissimi nobis
                        marchionis <persName key="#Marquis/duke"><name ref="Burcardus"
                                >Burchardi</name></persName> ceterorumque fidelium nostrorum
                        abbatiam <orgName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Commutatio #Placitum/iudicatum #Rivers #Fisheries #Saltworks #Wine #Oil #Hay/fodder #Operae #Angaria #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Exemption #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte Marie</orgName> in <placeName
                            ref="#places/4179">Pomposia</placeName> ab antecessore nostro imperatore
                            <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/7">Ottone</persName> a
                            <persName key="#Archbishops" ref="#people/1568">Federico</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1471"><placeName ref="#places/594"
                                >Rauennatis</placeName></orgName> aecclesiae archiepiscopo iuxta
                        utriusque <rs key="#Placitum/iudicatum">placitum</rs> ad imperialis
                        subiectionem proprietatis <rs key="#Commutatio">concambiatam</rs> ac postea
                        ab <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/130">Heinrico</persName>
                        nostro altero antecessore corroboratam et ab <persName key="#Marquis/duke"
                            ref="#people/3">Ugone</persName> marchione magnifice ditatam et per avum
                        nostrum <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/261">Chonradum</persName>
                        imperatorem boneque memoriae genitorem nostrum imperatorem <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/237">Heinricum</persName> successione
                        imperii et legali iure hereditatam, dehinc eodem iure ad <rs
                            key="Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">nostre dominationis manum</rs> receptam
                        cum omnibus suis pertinentiis, quicquid videlicet predicta abbatia per
                        aliquod munimen cartarum vel traditionum detinet vel eidem pertinet ab
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1100">ecclesia
                            Romana</orgName> et Rauennate aut ab aliqua alia seu etiam quicquid iure
                        proprietatis detinet aut acquirere in futuro potuerit, id est totam <rs
                            key="#Islands">insulam</rs> integram a primo latere <placeName
                            ref="#places/4657">Pado</placeName> percurrente in <rs key="#Sea"
                            >mare</rs>, a secundo latere <rs key="#Shores">litus maris</rs>, a
                        tertio vero latere <placeName ref="#places/3563">Gauro</placeName>; et <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscariam</rs> que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fisheries #Ports" ref="#estates/2465"><geogName
                                key="#Fisheries #Ports" ref="#estates/2457"><placeName
                                    key="#Fisheries #Ports">Uolana</placeName></geogName></geogName>
                        cum <rs key="#Ports">portu</rs> integro a <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3575">Badarino</placeName> ex utrisque
                        partibus usque in mare et <rs key="#Massae">massam</rs> que dicitur
                            <geogName key="#Massae" ref="#estates/2454"><placeName key="#Massae"
                                ref="#places/3559">Lacus sanctus</placeName></geogName> cum
                        lateribus suis et cum <rs key="#Fisheries">pischaria</rs> que vocatur
                            <geogName key="#Fisheries" ref="#estates/2455"
                                ><placeName>Tidin[i]</placeName></geogName>, a primo latere <rs
                            key="#Fundi">fundo</rs> qui vocatur <geogName key="#Fundi"
                            ref="#estates/3919"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                            >Grecule</placeName></geogName> et fundo qui vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Fundi" ref="#estates/2494"><placeName key="#Fundi"
                                ref="#places/3520">Corna Ceruina</placeName></geogName> et fluvio
                        qui vocatur <placeName key="#Rivers #Confina" ref="#places/3568"
                            >Cisi</placeName> et <rs key="#Canals">canale</rs> qui vocatur
                            <placeName key="#Canals #Confinia" ref="#places/3569">Curlo</placeName>,
                        a secundo latere <rs key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">valle</rs> que vocatur
                            <placeName key="#Confinia #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos" ref="#places/4681"
                            >Farulle</placeName> et fluvio qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers #Confinia" ref="#places/3564">Conca Agathe</placeName>
                        descendente in Gaurum, a tertio latere ipso Gauro, a quarto vero Pado
                        percurrente; insuper <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs> unam integram que vocatur
                            <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/2487"><placeName key="#Curtes"
                                ref="#places/4619">Hustolatus</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Plebs">plebe</rs> sua et aliam que vocatur <geogName key="#Curtes"
                            ref="#estates/3920"><placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/4695"
                                >Baoria</placeName></geogName> et curtem aliam quae vocatur
                            <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/3921"><placeName key="#Curtes"
                                >Ultra canalem</placeName></geogName> cum omnibus ad monasterium
                            <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1474">sancte Mariae
                            in xenodochio</orgName> pertinentibus et cum omnibus, quae predicte
                        abbatie Ugo marchio filius <persName><name ref="Hubertus"
                            >Huberti</name></persName> dedit, quicquid etiam habet aut acquirere
                        poterit infra Padum et <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4646"
                            >Atesim</placeName> fluvium vel infra Padum et <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/3588">Sandalum</placeName> et quantacumque in apostolice
                        sedis privilegio releguntur, verum etiam queque habet aut acquirere poterit
                        in civitate Rauenna et infra totum <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/485"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2449">Comiaclensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3538"><geogName
                                key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2435"
                            >Gauellensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/80"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/84"
                                >Ferariensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/38"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/208"
                                >Mutinensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/7"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2439"
                                >Bononiensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2409"
                                >Corneliensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3513"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2458"
                                >Fauentinum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/3515"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2459"
                                >Liuiensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/4602"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2480"
                                >Popiliensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                            ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1479"
                                >Cesenatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName key="#Comitatus"
                                ><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/1478"
                                >Montemferetranum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1806"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1480">Ariminensem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1807"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2482">Pensauriensem</geogName></placeName> et
                            <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1808"><geogName
                                key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/2481">Fanensem</geogName></placeName>
                        et <placeName key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1812"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2371">Urbinatem</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/1803"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1481">Castellanum</geogName></placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/2752"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2462">Perusinum</geogName></placeName> et in omnibus
                        quoque locis cum areis edificiis <rs key="#Castle">castris</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludibus</rs> salictis <rs key="#Oil"
                            >olivetis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> vallibus planitiebus aquis aquarumque
                        decursibus piscationibus <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters"
                            >venationibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Saltworks">salinis</rs> et cum omni utilitate, que vel nominari
                        vel scribi potest, <rs key="#Exemption">ab omni subiectione archiepiscoporum
                            Rauennatum excutimus</rs>, ut regalis in perpetuum sit nullis
                        dominantium personis subiecta. Sintque <rs key="#Monks">monachi</rs> eius ab
                        omni secularis <rs key="#Operae">servitii</rs> infestatione securi et ab
                        omni <rs key="#Angaria">angaria</rs> sive <rs key="#Fodrum">fodro</rs> tam
                        nostro quamque <rs key="#Missus_regis">missorum nostrorum</rs> seu omnium
                        secularium potestatum cum suis hominibus remoti; qui de suis, qualem
                        voluerint, <rs key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs> eligant ab episcopo <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1498">Comiaclense</orgName> consecrandum, qui,
                        si sibi pro pecunia vel aliqua humana potestate molestus esse voluerit,
                        veniat ad archiepiscopum Rauennatem ab eo benedicendus; et si hoc in isto
                        quod in illo invenerit, ad qualemcumque episcopum voluerit causa
                        consecrationis properet. Si quis autem hoc preceptum imperiale nostrum
                        infringere presumpserit, componat <rs key="#Penalty">ducentas libras auri
                            cocti</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere nostre</rs> et
                        medietatem <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">prelibate
                            abbatie</rs>. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc imperialem paginam manu
                        propria roboratam sigillari iussimus. Signum domni Heinrici tercii (M.)
                        Romanorum invictissimi imperatoris augusti. Herimannus Coloniensis
                        archiepiscopus et archicancellarius recognovit. Raginaldus subcancellarius
                        scripsi. Data non. octubris anno dominice+ incarnationis MLXXXXV, indictione
                        IIII, anno autem ordinationis domni Heinrici tertii imperatoris XLI, regni
                        vero XXXIIII, imperii vero XI; actum <placeName ref="#places/620"
                            >Garde</placeName>; feliciter in dei nomine amen. (B. D.)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>MGH DD H IV, pp. 606-608, n. 450.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Enrico IV conferma a Pomposa i diritti, le dipendenze, la libera elezione
                    dell'abate e prende il monastero sotto la sua tutela. Documento esemplato su MGH
                    DD H III, 193.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
